13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showPrevMessage?topicID=2634.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showNextMessage?topicID=2634.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Author</font></td><td valign=top  class=headings><font color=#333399>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usineras.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sineras</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/16/01 9:43:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2634.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Summoning</span><hr size=1> Just getting to a level where this is becomming a real 'day ruiner'<br>
<br>
Any strategies to combat this?<br>
<br>
Can you get over 200 in magic resist and have a reasonable chance of resisting the spell.<br>
<br>
Like can you snare, run, root yourself, then root mob and dot/ nuke?<br>
(BTW a nice touch to spell casting would be an innate ability to cancel out any spell you cast on yourself, I mean you cast it yourself, on yourself, right?).<br>
<br>
Why can't we summon? Etc...<br>
<br>
Can you outrun the spell?<br>
<br>
Any help in this matter would be greatly appreciated.<br>
<br>
Sineras Fizzalot, 55 Preserver  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uevilhobbitjarvalor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evil Hobbit Jarvalor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/16/01 9:46:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2634.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Summoning</span><hr size=1> The only way to not get summoned is to clear you agro or kill it. Whether it be camping, zoning whatever.  You can't resist summoning, if youre rooted, you'll still get summoned.  My advice - don't fight summoning mobs solo ;)  And no you cant click off root if you accidently cast it on yourself  <p><img src=http://www.raarcentral.com/zizar/jarvalor01.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uandaerynwindstrider.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Andaeryn Windstrider</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/18/01 5:19:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2634.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Summoning</span><hr size=1> I personally like getting summoned (In Kael anyways). My saying is &quot;I don't feel I've contributed toa  raid until I get summoned at least once.&quot; :)<br>
<br>
Andaeryn Windstider,<br>
Druid of Tunare 51st Circle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/19/01 3:31:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2634.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/smallface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Summoning</span><hr size=1> Summoned once is no big deal. Even twice or three times, no big deal. It's when you get summoned and your aggro is so high that you are basically chain-summoned and smashed dead very, very quickly -- no tank can pull the mob off you. <br>
<br>
On the other hand, you might have to sacrifice yourself to save someone else :P. A good way to save an enchanter is to stack debuffs on a mob. :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utrienatwobooks.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Triena Twobooks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/20/01 10:56:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2634.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Summings Up</span><hr size=1> Geting summoned is fun...not that you should aim for it to happen on a raid, but hay if you are summoned its sometimes impresses the tanks that should know better.<br>
<br>
2 times when you dont want to be summoned...<br>
<br>
1.  Everyones going DOWN! the mob is just moping up evereone on the agro list after all the tanks are dead and the monks are FD, when you get summoned in this situation your are summoned to an insta death.<br>
<br>
2.  The ubermob_01 gates, then starts summoning the raid party, one by one.  Ive been on raids in Keal and ive seen only one person get summoned after a gate then it ignored the rest like we were out of Velious agro range or something.<br>
<br>
As stated above, no its not resistable, and yes i agree, mobs having the ability to summon is VI's way of cheeting :)  If the ability is avalable to mobs, then why dont we get it post 50? eh? hehe even the melee types summon.  Its like changeing the laws of physics. :D <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaslethalo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>maslethalo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/20/01 6:57:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2634.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Summings Up</span><hr size=1> Getting summoned as a druid can quite often be bad in a raid situation as mentioned above in kael.  If you get summoned early on in say a Vindi Fight you probably contributed alright.  You contributed to insure that your raid just failed.  <br>
<br>
The best druid is one that knows how to control agro.  Sure you will get summoned from time to time, but there are several situations where this is very bad. <p><p><img src=http://www.slip.net/~maximus/roguesig.jpg>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uperkynipples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Perk Ynipples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/1/02 8:41:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2634.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Summings Up</span><hr size=1> Getting Summoned is fine... getting hit and running away from the mob is not.  If you get summoned and start getting beat on... Stand there and take it, and don't expect the cleric to save your arse.  If you run and the mob chases you, it makes it that much harder for the main tank to reagro. If the mob's not on the main tank it means the raid has to spend more mana healing whomever it is beating on, or rebuffing the dead casters.  Best for one over-debuffing/nuking druid to die, than for the mob to kill you, and then decide that cleric that tried to heal you should die next.<br>
<br>
Mobs over a certain level (now lower level mobs can be designed with the ability to summon... but I have only seen this in SoL) summon every 10-20 seconds (I beleive this is a fixed value depending on zone, anyone care to comment?)  They typically summon whomever is at the top of the agro list if they aren't already in melee range of them.  That's why it's important to make sure that the tank is at the top of the agro list, and not the druid =)<br>
<br>
I realize that druid spells are very high agro, and I'm of the opinion (based on some actual tests with respawning mobs) that if all else is equal, druids will be at the top of the agro list automatically.  One of the most important things you can learn though, is how to control the amount of agro you pull by timing your spells.  It's something of an art form because of all the variables involved.  A fun way to practice however is to actually have a summoning contest with other druids on the raid.  The first rule of this contest is that if you are summoned, you stand and take your beating until the mob reagro's the tank... no running =)  You score one point for every time a mob summons you.  The catch is, that if you die to anything less than a total wipe... your score goes back to zero.  The goal of course is to have the highest score at the end of the raid...  Its very amusing and a whole lot of fun to figure out exactly what you can cast when to get summoned but not beat on... =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukalinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/1/02 7:59:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2634.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/azurecrayon/wolf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Summings Up</span><hr size=1> actually, standing there and letting something beat you into submission after being summoned is not neccessarily the correct way to go.  you should move away from the mob slowly.  a lot of mobs have a range proximity agro factor, which means you are just as tasty as the tank that is taunting them and it will just eat whoever is closest, and summoning puts you as close as you can get.  so after being summoned, turn off attack if its on, dont cast any offensive spells or heals, and move away slowly until the mobs attention returns to the tank.  this should be carefully done so as not to pull the mob out of a needed position should it be an frontal ae'ing or riposting mob.<br>
<br>
the rate at which a mob summons is determined by the zone, different zones have different summon refresh rates.  its also a melee skill for mobs, not a spell.  its instantaneous with no casting time and requires no mana.<br>
<br>
also if you are getting high on the agro list vs a summoning mob, dont sit down =)  they often see that as a free invitation to summon you to their feet and pummel you.  but usually standing back up as soon as you are summoned with remove you from their immediate agro so you dont get hit. <p>-K<br>
